This paper is about improving the performance of neural machine translation systems by contextualizing and symbolizing word embeddings. The paper focuses on natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which are typically covered in the Computer Science sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a bag-of-words representation and typed symbols to improve the translation quality, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses experiments to evaluate the proposed approaches, which may fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) that often involves empirical evaluations.
